<div class=3D"WordSection1">
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Hello Rafaella,<o:p>=
</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Responding to your e=
mail below.
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I understand that Da=
vid has responded to acknowledge that there are more contents to schedule an=
d appraise and he is continuing to do so.<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">You have sked me for=
 Towers approval for you to appoint a Structural Engineer to assess the prop=
erty. There is no requirement for this to be done. As explained in my previo=
us email =E2=80=93 we have attended with
 a technical building Consultant who is well qualified to make the necessary=
 observations and issue documents and instructions on the repairs that are r=
equired to complete repairs to your home. I have copied the capability state=
ment directly below which I shared
 with you last night. Noting that ASURNZ will refer to a CPEng qualified str=
uctural engineer only if required after having completed their report. We wi=
ll of course share the report we receive from ASURNZ with you.<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">To that end Tower wi=
ll not engage a CPEng qualified structural engineer, until instructed to do s=
o by ASURNZ.
<u>Tower will not be obliged to reimburse you if you chose to do this for yo=
urself.</u>
<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have included an e=
xtract below from your policy wording which explains the policy response pos=
ition on this issue. Of most relevance here is the prefacing wording which s=
tates that: =E2=80=98 We will pay where necessary
 =E2=80=98. Please refer to policy wording extract below.<o:p></o:p></span><=
/p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I have also attached=
 a copy of the full policy wording for your further reference. &nbsp;<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:10.0pt;font-f=
amily:&quot;Arial&quot;,sans-serif;color:#275317;mso-fareast-language:EN-US"=
>Further, considering the knowledge and experience provided by ASURNZ person=
nel regarding the assessment of fire damaged
 timber framed buildings, including my knowledge and experience, I doubt the=
re would be any additional benefit gained by engaging a structural engineer f=
or this claim.&nbsp; However, should any design requirements that sit outsid=
e the scope limitations of NZS 3604:2011
 and that require specific engineering design become apparent during scoping=
 of repairs, I confirm that we will in that instance seek engineering design=
 from a suitably experienced Chartered Professional Engineer (CPEng).</span>=
<o:p></o:p></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span lang=3D"EN-NZ" style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>=
&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><div>&lt;image001.pn=
g&gt;</div></span><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">I would like to carr=
y on with our provided process and have the upstairs cleaned and the gib-boa=
rd wall linings removed to enable us to inspect the exterior wall cavities t=
o complete a thorough assessment
 of the repairs required. Can I have your approval to instruct Davids team t=
o do so?<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Best Regards,<o:p></=
o:p></span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt">Grant. <o:p></o:p></=
span></p>
<p class=3D"MsoNormal"><span style=3D"font-size:11.0pt"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></s=
pan></p>
